<i>noun</i>: 한시 [한시], 한순간 [한순간], 촌음 [초ː늠], 촌각 [촌ː각], 찰나 [찰라], 잠시 [잠ː시], 잠깐 [잠깐], 일시 [일씨], 일분일초 [일분일초], 일각 [일각], 시각 [시각], 순식간 [순식깐], 순간 [순간], 삽시간 [삽씨간], 간발 [간ː발] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>한시 [한시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. same time</dd><br>
<dd>같은 시각.</dd><br>
<dd>The same time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. moment</dd><br>
<dd>잠깐의 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>A brief period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>한순간 [한순간]</dt><br>
<dd>instant; moment; a flash of time; being in the wink of an eye</dd><br>
<dd>아주 짧은 시간 동안.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short period of time</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>촌음 [초ː늠]</dt><br>
<dd>moment; instant</dd><br>
<dd>매우 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>촌각 [촌ː각]</dt><br>
<dd>moment; instant</dd><br>
<dd>매우 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>찰나 [찰라]</dt><br>
<dd>1. instant</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이나 현상이 일어나는 바로 그때.</dd><br>
<dd>The very moment at which something happens.</dd><br>
<dd>2. instant; moment</dd><br>
<dd>불교에서, 매우 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>In Buddhism, a very short period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>잠시 [잠ː시]</dt><br>
<dd>moment; short while</dd><br>
<dd>잠깐 동안.</dd><br>
<dd>A short time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>잠깐 [잠깐]</dt><br>
<dd>while; moment</dd><br>
<dd>아주 짧은 시간 동안.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>일시 [일씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. moment; brief time period</dd><br>
<dd>잠깐의 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>A short time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. one time</dd><br>
<dd>같은 때.</dd><br>
<dd>The same time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>일분일초 [일분일초]</dt><br>
<dd>second; moment</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 아주 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A very short period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>일각 [일각]</dt><br>
<dd>1. moments; second</dd><br>
<dd>한 시간의 4분의 1.</dd><br>
<dd>A quarter of an hour.</dd><br>
<dd>2. second; moment</dd><br>
<dd>아주 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>시각 [시각]</dt><br>
<dd>1. time; hour</dd><br>
<dd>연속되는 시간의 어느 한 지점.</dd><br>
<dd>A certain single point in the continuous flow of time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. moment; minute; second</dd><br>
<dd>얼마 안 되는 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>순식간 [순식깐]</dt><br>
<dd>instant; moment</dd><br>
<dd>눈을 한 번 깜빡하거나 숨을 한 번 쉴 만큼의 아주 짧은 동안.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short moment in which one can blink once or take one breath.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>순간 [순간]</dt><br>
<dd>1. moment</dd><br>
<dd>아주 짧은 시간 동안.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short period.</dd><br>
<dd>2. instant</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 일어나거나 어떤 행동이 이루어지는 바로 그때.</dd><br>
<dd>The exact time when something happens or an action is done.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>삽시간 [삽씨간]</dt><br>
<dd>instant; moment; a flash of time; being in the wink of an eye</dd><br>
<dd>매우 짧은 시간.</dd><br>
<dd>A very short period of time</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>간발 [간ː발]</dt><br>
<dd>moment; little</dd><br>
<dd>아주 잠시 또는 아주 적음을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A term referring to a very short time or a very small quantity.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>